Joanne gives me another choice--retake with the pawn or the Queen.  I felt that taking with the pawn would make my position passive, but I could certainly be wrong.  I just looked at the pawns at d4 and c4, the N at c3 and the Q at a4 and decided the white's attack could be too strong.  Additionally, by retaking with my Q, I attack both c4 and g2.
